        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 5:31PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 531 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Sisterdale, or 13 miles west of Blanco, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kendalia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
